"v. 流口水；奉承；n. 口水 【英】 v.流口水, 渴望(drool, slobber);n.口水(saliva) 【记】 分割记忆：slave(奴 隸)＋er v. 流(口水) = drool; 奉承 = fawn; n 口水 【记】slave(n 奴隸), r: 奴隸的正面特征就是留着口水奉承. 【参】slobber(v 淌口水; n 口水) 【记】slave 奴隸总是流着口水谄媚，这就是所说的奴性；saliva 口水, 唾液 【相关】slobber ,drool 淌口水 slaver (v.)  ""dribble from the mouth,"" early 14c., from Old Norse slafra ""to slaver,"" probably imitative (compare slobber (v.)). Related: Slavered; slavering. The noun is from early 14c. slaver (n.)  ""ship in the slave trade,"" 1830, agent noun from slave (v.). Meaning ""person in the slave trade"" is from 1842."
